content:
Invoke a Data Mapper Transform to restructure, rename, and convert data. Unlike Data Mapper Extracts and Loads, Transforms do not read or write Salesforce data.

If the Data Mapper Transform doesn't already exist, you can create it by clicking Create New Data Mapper immediately after dragging the Data Mapper Transform into the OmniScript structure panel.

Drag the Data Mapper Transform Action into the OmniScript's structure panel.
To select the Data Mapper Transform to be called, click in the Data Mapper Interface field and select from the list. You can type in the field to filter the list.
Use the Send/Response Transformations properties to trim or rename the input JSON so it has the structure the Data Mapper Transform expects. Or you can trim or rename the output JSON for a subsequent OmniScript step.

Omnistudio Data Mapper Transform Action Properties
This page contains information on Data Mapper Transform Action Properties.

See also: Populate a DocuSign Template Using an Omnistudio Data Mapper Transform, Create an Omnistudio Data Mapper Interface to Map OmniScript Data to a PDF.
title: Omnistudio Data Mapper Transform Action
